What will dominate TV news headlines in 2050?
As part of the BBC's What If? season of programmes, we commissioned a week of news reports that take a light-hearted look at the future.
We kick off with a tale of the first birth in space and an unfortunate accident at the cryonics plant.
Have we got it right? Could these stories feature in the headlines in 2050?
